      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The difference lies between healthy cultural identity and exclusionary nationalism; the latter actively seeks to diminish or oppress those outside its defined borders. While all groups have boundaries, nationalism weaponizes those boundaries to justify hierarchy and discrimination. A society built on shared civic principles, like democracy and the rule of law, can achieve profound stability without resorting to the divisive fervor of ethnic or national supremacy.",
      "source": "target",
